  • 19 Sports Modes & IP68 Waterproof : The watch has 1.5 inch big screen and is easy for child to touch and use. The watch supports 19 outdoor and indoor sports modes (including running, football, swimming, etc.). Choose from selected modes on the watch or add through 'H Band' APP to set your training schedule and track their workout stats. Don't worry about the proper use of the watch even through washes his/her hands, goes swimming, or does other exercises because of IP68 water resistance and drainage
  • 24 HOURS NON-STOP HEALTH TRACKING :The smart watch uses high-performance optical sensors to act as a fitness tracker in a timely and accurate manner, recording your daily walking steps, distance and calories, continuously monitoring their heart rate and sleep quality. Then show detailed data to help you build up a good lifestyle
  • SMART NOTIFICATIONS VIA BLUETOOTH :The watch support multiple smart alerts, including incoming calls, SMS, SNS messages (Facebook, WhatsApp, LINE, etc.), daily reminders, etc., which make your life have more convenience and you won't miss any important information. Note: the watch does not support SIM cards. The watch uses Bluetooth to connect to the phone and does not support a separate WiFi connection
  • LONG-LASTING BATTERY & MAGNETIC CHARGING :Can last about 6 days of daily use after 2 hours of charging time and is compatible with most android and iOS phones (android 5.0+ and iOS 10+). You may also set the brightness, vibration, and wake function on/off, and easily charge it with the included magnetic charger. Notice: please fully charge for about two hours for the first use
  • No APP/PHONE REQUIRED :The smart watch can be used separatedly without relying on a phone or app. Most basic application scenarios can be operated by the watch. There will be more extended function via APP/Phone

      This is a cute little watch. I got it for my two year old niece who is obsessed with my Apple Watch. The band on this watch is baby pink colored silicone and it's very soft, making it a good fit for her toddler skin. It does not pinch like a watch sometimes does and has... See more
      This is a cute little watch. I got it for my two year old niece who is obsessed with my Apple Watch. The band on this watch is baby pink colored silicone and it's very soft, making it a good fit for her toddler skin. It does not pinch like a watch sometimes does and has a decent quality for the photos on the face of the watch. The reason I'm knocking the product rating down to 3.5/4.0 stars is because of the app. "H Band" is what it's called and it is a bit of a pain to navigate. The whole reason I purchased this watch is for my niece to be able to have a picture of herself on her watch like on mine. It is difficult to change the watch face to a personalized photo and you can only have one personalized photo at a time. If you want to change the watch face you have to navigate through the app every time. The watch does have nice features, such as sleep tracking, heart rate, pedometer, things like that. I know my toddler niece could use these features down the road, but for now it's more of an accessory for her. It would be a better fit for an adult who has access to a phone and can use the other features. It's a decent option for a budget watch, which is something I was looking for for her.

      4.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
      A great first watch for a child. Very comfortable and waterproof!
      Reviewed in Canada on October 12, 2023
      2.
      I am a huge fan and collector of smartwatches. I have owned sub-$100 off-brand watches and $500+ name-brand smartwatches. As technology has gotten better so have the smartwatches. They are now all packed with a lot of features that were not available not too long ago. I saw... See more
      I am a huge fan and collector of smartwatches. I have owned sub-$100 off-brand watches and $500+ name-brand smartwatches. As technology has gotten better so have the smartwatches. They are now all packed with a lot of features that were not available not too long ago. I saw this smartwatch which is geared towards kids and I wanted to see if this would be something that a child could use. I ordered the blue version of this watch. It arrived in a very nice giftable box. Included in the box is the watch, a USB-A to magnet charging cable, and a user manual. The watch charges easily by attaching the magnetic end of the charging cable to the watch. It holds firmly. To get the most out of the watch you need to download the app "H band" from the Apple or Google Play stores to your phone. The watch pairs very quickly with the app. This smartwatch has a 1.5-inch screen on it. This is a very nice size for a child's wrist. I have seen kid's smartwatches that have adult-sized screens and they look too big. The silicone band comes attached and is very comfortable. It has a lot of holes in it so it can be tightened around a child's small wrist. The watch has one button which you press to access the menu. You can then scroll through the various functions with the nicely responsive touch screen or the button. The menus are intuitive and easy for a child to maneuver through. As for apps and functions, this watch has all of the expected apps like activity monitoring, heart rate monitoring, step count, alarm, notifications from various apps, and much more. The watch is rated IP68 for being dustproof and able to be submerged in water with no problem. This is great for a kid who may forget their watch is on at bath time or they may drop it into the water. It's nice knowing water will not harm the watch. The watch holds a charge for around a week which is nice so you do not have to charge it every day like you do with some watches. I am very happy with this watch and it would make a great first watch for a child. I have attached a video showing me scrolling through the functions.
      I am a huge fan and collector of smartwatches. I have owned sub-$100 off-brand watches and $500+ name-brand smartwatches. As technology has gotten better so have the smartwatches. They are now all packed with a lot of features that were not available not too long ago.

      I saw this smartwatch which is geared towards kids and I wanted to see if this would be something that a child could use.

      I ordered the blue version of this watch. It arrived in a very nice giftable box. Included in the box is the watch, a USB-A to magnet charging cable, and a user manual.

      The watch charges easily by attaching the magnetic end of the charging cable to the watch. It holds firmly.

      To get the most out of the watch you need to download the app "H band" from the Apple or Google Play stores to your phone.

      The watch pairs very quickly with the app.

      This smartwatch has a 1.5-inch screen on it. This is a very nice size for a child's wrist. I have seen kid's smartwatches that have adult-sized screens and they look too big.

      The silicone band comes attached and is very comfortable. It has a lot of holes in it so it can be tightened around a child's small wrist.

      The watch has one button which you press to access the menu. You can then scroll through the various functions with the nicely responsive touch screen or the button.

      The menus are intuitive and easy for a child to maneuver through.

      As for apps and functions, this watch has all of the expected apps like activity monitoring, heart rate monitoring, step count, alarm, notifications from various apps, and much more.

      The watch is rated IP68 for being dustproof and able to be submerged in water with no problem. This is great for a kid who may forget their watch is on at bath time or they may drop it into the water. It's nice knowing water will not harm the watch.

      The watch holds a charge for around a week which is nice so you do not have to charge it every day like you do with some watches.

      I am very happy with this watch and it would make a great first watch for a child.
      I have attached a video showing me scrolling through the functions.
